50|$|TRESOR is a {{software}} approach {{that seeks to}} resolve this insecurity by storing and manipulating <b>encryption</b> <b>keys</b> almost exclusively on the CPU alone, and in registers accessible at ring 0 (the highest privilege level) only—the exception being the brief period of initial calculation {{at the start of}} a session. This ensures that <b>encryption</b> <b>keys</b> are almost never available via user space or following a cold boot attack. TRESOR is written as a kernel patch that stores <b>encryption</b> <b>keys</b> in the x86 debug registers, and uses on-the-fly round key generation, atomicity, and blocking of usual ptrace access to the debug registers for security.|$|R
